eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Several people have been evacuated and many more have been displaced following heavy rains in KwaZulu-Natal. KZN disaster management teams are on high alert as the situation remains volatile in several parts of the province. Last month, deadly floods claimed over 400 lives. eNCA’s Manqoba Mchunu shares more details in the video above.